data.text: @umbrellaes Worst warhorse you could skate to and yuzu using Gerard butlers vocals made it worse. It's his weakest program but to be fair POTO is 99 percent of skaters weakest programs since most of them use bad music cuts from the 04 soundtrack. Akiko's is the only really good poto imo.

@umbrellaes I do NOT understand what is wrong with that man, not wanting to skate to P&P. 

...there's a part of my shipper brain that thinks it's his petty vengeance for her not wanting them to go public. But that's just too cruel. I mean, who DOES that?! 😂
@fairwinds_09 it’s a poto program MADE for vm but we’ll probably never see it.....unless they use it as their 2020-2021 fd before using p&p as their 2021-2022 fd :-)))

@umbrellaes YESSSS. Think what a sizzling ice dance program you could create to that one...all the possessiveness and scorching glances and sliding hands over places that probably should remain untouched in a public arena...

Shame V/M never thought of doing that one, really. ;)

@fairwinds_09 honestly, learn to be lonely would be a refreshing addition to any poto program! most people just use a blend of music of the night/overture/think of me but I think anyone attempting a poto program should search for deeper music cuts. where are my point of no return programs?!!!

@umbrellaes Tbh, I would also be okay with Minnie Driver's "Learn To Be Lonely."

Although since that isn't actually part of Andrew Lloyd Webber's original score, I'm guessing it doesn't exactly count...
@fairwinds_09 I need to sit down with all skaters, coaches, and choreographers and give a presentation detailing why the 2004 movie soundtrack is only okay to use for its overture

@umbrellaes YUZU. HONEY. 

You are BETTER than this.
